article.description: — Charles Thompson's 14 points helped Towson defeat Robert Morris 66-62 on Sunday night.
article.headline: Thompson's 14 lead Towson past Robert Morris 66-62
article.linkText: Thompson's 14 lead Towson past Robert Morris 66-62
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- — Charles Thompson's 14 points helped Towson defeat Robert Morris 66-62 on Sunday night. Thompson had 10 rebounds for the Tigers (2-1). Tyler Tejada scored 13 points while going 4 of 8 and 4 of 5 from the free-throw line, and added seven rebounds. Christian May had 11 points and shot 5 for 10, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc. Justice Williams led the way for the Colonials (1-2) with 16 points. Robert Morris also got 15 points from Stephaun Walker. TJ Wainwright also had 13 points. Towson's next game is Thursday against No. 7 Houston at the Charleston Classic. Robert Morris visits Wisconsin on Friday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
